es that there are some grounds for optimism about a future that could be both more feminist and more socialist.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminismxSocial aspects. 0aSocialism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh  ablack feminism.  aconservative feminism.  afeminism.  aintersectionality.  aneoliberal feminism.  apatriarchy.  asex/gender distinction.  asocialist feminism.  atrans women.  atransgender.1 aBryson, Valerie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packagez978311128198840uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613850740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526138507423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526138507/original  a978-3-11-128198-8  Manchester University Press 2021 eBook-Packageb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles